modules.description: Provides functions for parsing and validating error messages from a specific logging format, including extracting timestamps, severity levels, and raw message content. Operates on strings and custom record types representing parsed log entries. Used to filter and transform error logs during system diagnostics.

The module provides assertion operations for testing, validating expected outcomes against actual results with customizable checks on values, lists, exceptions, and specific types like strings and integers. It includes tools for constructing and managing test suites using functional combinators, working with test cases, suites, fixtures, and supervisors to organize testing workflows. These capabilities are suited for scenarios requiring precise result verification and structured test hierarchy management.
